---
/**
 * Standalone claim that leads into the Método Zil section — brutalist scale.
 *
 * Spacing is deliberately asymmetric, and that is the rhythm working, not
 * drifting: `pt-section` gives the standard half-gap above (Projects supplies
 * the matching half), while below is ZERO. Método Zil is viewport-pinned — its
 * stage is min-h-100svh with centred content, so it already opens with
 * (100svh − content) / 2 of space above its logo. Any padding added here is
 * stacked on top of that. Let the pinned stage own the space below; do not
 * add `pb-*` here.
 */
---

<section>
  <div
    class="mx-auto w-full max-w-8xl px-6 pt-section text-center tablet:px-8 desktop:px-12"
    data-reveal-group
  >
    <h2 class="statement-heading tracking-[-0.04em]" data-reveal>
      Una comunicación visual clara es{" "}
      <span
        class="bg-primary-dark px-[0.15em] whitespace-nowrap text-accent"
        data-reveal="band"
        data-reveal-delay="0.45"
        ><span data-band-text>diferenciación.</span></span
      >
    </h2>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .statement-heading {
    font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 10vw, 7rem);
    line-height: 1.1;
    font-weight: 600;
  }
</style>
